          </protein>
          <protein>
            <id type="integer">1170</id>
            <name>Ephrin type-A receptor 2</name>
            <uniprot-id>P29317</uniprot-id>
            <description>Receptor for members of the ephrin-A family. Binds to ephrin-A1, -A3, -A4 and -A5. Plays an important role in angiogenesis and tumor neovascularization. The recruitement of VAV2, VAV3 and PI3-kinase p85 subunit by phosphorylated EPHA2 is critical for EFNA1-induced RAC1 GTPase activation and vascular endothelial cell migration and assembly. Induces apoptosis in a TP53/p53-independent, caspase-8-dependent manner</description>
